  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the binchotan grill to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Season the serrano ham slices with salt, Kashmiri red chili powder, cumin seeds, and coriander powder.",
    "Brush the grill with ghee to prevent sticking.",
    "Grill the serrano ham slices for 2-3 minutes per side or until slightly charred.",
    "While the ham is grilling, heat ghee in a pan over medium heat and sauté the ginger, garlic, and green chilies until fragrant.",
    "Add Bhuna Masala to the pan and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add lime juice and stir to combine.",
    "To assemble the thali, place a grilled serrano ham slice on a plate, followed by a spoonful of the sautéed ginger mixture, and finally a sprinkle of chopped cilantro.",
    "Brush the grill with ghee to prevent sticking, then grill the baby spinach leaves until wilted.",
    "Garnish the thali with wilted spinach leaves and serve immediately.",
    "Let the dish rest for 5 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to meld together.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
